==German==
===Etymology===
From the notion that turkish people supposedly smell like [[caraway]], also onomatopoetically because of the high frequency of the umlaut "ü" in the Turkish language, e.g. in ''güle güle'' - "goodbye" (Ironically, caraway is much more frequent in German than in Turkish cooking).

===Noun===
'''Kümmeltürke''' ''f''
# very derogative and xenophobic term for a [[turkish]] person, or rather anyone coming from a culture that has food rich in spices
